      "name": "Low-flow bench hemolysis comparison at 3 L/min, 3000 RPM",
      "description": "Experimental hemolysis index measured at low-flow laminar-dominated operating point (3 L/min, 3000 RPM). CFD prediction of normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurement. Agreement within 8%. This operating point falls in the laminar regime (Re < 2300 in volute passages) and does not exercise turbulent flow conditions."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-002-mid-flow-bench",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mid-flow bench hemolysis comparison at 5 L/min, 3500 RPM",
      "description": "Experimental hemolysis index measured at nominal CPB operating point (5 L/min, 3500 RPM). CFD prediction compared against in-vitro measurement. Agreement within 12%. Flow conditions at this point are in the transitional regime; the simplified laminar model produces acceptable aggregate hemolysis predictions but does not resolve turbulent stress contributions."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-003-pressure-head",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Pump pressure-head curve validation across 5 operating points",
      "description": "Simulated pressure-head curve compared against manufacturer bench test data across 5 flow-speed combinations. Mean error 4.1%. Validation confirms hydraulic performance prediction but does not assess turbulence-driven shear stress distributions or their contribution to hemolysis."
    }
