      "acceptanceCriteria": "Governing equations and constitutive models must be documented and justified for the COU physics at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Incompressible Navier-Stokes equations with Newtonian blood viscosity (mu = 0.0035 Pa·s) and the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model are documented. The model adopts a simplified laminar flow formulation. Turbulence modeling is not included; the rationale states that at the primary design operating point (5 L/min, 3500 RPM) bulk Reynolds numbers in major passages are below 4000 and laminar assumptions are considered adequate. No formal fidelity trade study quantifying the impact of turbulence exclusion on hemolysis prediction was conducted. Gradation 2 requirement for documentation is met."
    },
